description: 1960 Cadillac Coupe DeVille
One of the most striking Fins ever put on cars of this era.  They are Tall, Well Appointed with Stainless, and Sharp!
This is a Barn Find from a Private Long Term Collection where 10 plus Cadillacs were all oiled up to keep from rusting and parked in the barn.  There it stayed for many years.
This particular car was put away back in the late 80's and it sat all this time with very little and occasional inspection by hired maintenance mechanic until he too stopped showing due to age.
This collection was a very exciting find of fin cars.

This vehicle,,, we drained the oil, cleaned off, inspected, and either replaced or brought back to life the vitals and now the powerful 390ci 325HP breathes again.  The Caddy Starts, Stops, and the Power Accessories are Working!
Tires are Vintage Wide Whites wrap around beautiful Factory Wire Wheel Covers.
Undercarriage is solid and dry. Notice the trunk floor and pictures of underneath.
Interior is Original and shows a bit of wear as well as a bit of damage due to barn pests getting into it.
Notice the Vintage Original 'T-3' Headlights still on the Caddy and operational.
An easy tinkering will make this beautiful boulevard cruiser Bristol Again!
These are highly collectable and this particular Coupe DeVille will make an excellent addition to any Collection or Hobbyist.
Please feel free to contact us with any and all questions.
